# Matbench V2 Element Properties Results

This records the Matbench rerun with `PathTransformerNet --use_element_props`.
The input fold caches were reused, while all models were retrained with
`--force`.

## Summary

| Task | v1 no props MAE | v2 element props MAE | Delta | CGCNN | ALIGNN | Outcome |
|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|---|
| `matbench_log_kvrh` | `0.0689±0.0021` | `0.0688±0.0022` | `-0.0000` | `0.0712` | `0.0435` | tiny improvement, still beats CGCNN |
| `matbench_log_gvrh` | `0.0918±0.0023` | `0.0915±0.0039` | `-0.0003` | `0.0849` | `0.0514` | tiny improvement, still behind CGCNN |
| `matbench_dielectric` | `0.3967±0.0549` | `0.3744±0.0655` | `-0.0223` | `0.3306` | `0.1679` | clear improvement, still behind CGCNN |
| `matbench_phonons` | `41.6687±3.5686` | `47.1325±16.2309` | `+5.4638` | `36.8000` | `29.5000` | regression |

Negative delta means v2 improved MAE.

